---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About">
  <div class="prose" style="padding-top:3rem;max-width:var(--max)">
    <p style="font-size:2rem;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;margin-bottom:0.3rem">Linxi</p>
    <p style="color:var(--ink-faint);font-size:0.88rem;font-style:italic;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:2rem">
      Undergraduate student in Computer Science, Xi’an Jiaotong University
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--ink-faint);font-size:0.88rem;font-style:italic;margin-top:-1.5rem;margin-bottom:2rem">
      per somnia — through dreams
    </p>
    <hr />

    <p>I’ve probably always been someone who likes to dream—</p>
    <p>not just the kind you have in your sleep,</p>
    <p>but the kind about the future, the world, and what might be possible.</p>

    <p>I chose computer science partly because it feels closer to turning ideas into something real.</p>
    <p>Writing code and building things is just a way of trying those ideas out—</p>
    <p>some work, some don’t, but all of them count.</p>

    <p>I’m not used to speaking in absolutes,</p>
    <p>and I’m still figuring out what I really want to do.</p>
    <p>But for now, I’m still willing to think, to try,</p>
    <p>and to make things that don’t already exist.</p>

    <p>If there’s one thing that hasn’t changed,</p>
    <p>it’s probably that I still know how to dream.</p>

    <p>And maybe, in a very real world,</p>
    <p>we can keep a few unrealistic dreams alive.</p>
  </div>
</Base>